REPLACE ~99999~ ~The fall of the Throne of Bhaal closed a long chapter in the lives of Sirene and her beloved <CHARNAME>, but was also the beginning of a new life for the couple. hough <CHARNAME> did not care for the formality of marriage, the couple were bonded for life regardless, as they devoted every moment of their life to each others' happiness. Their tale had not yet ended however, as the couple would lead a chain of exciting adventures after ending their current journey, venturing the realms the way they desired to, without the burdens of either of their bloodlines. The couple would grow weary of the demanding nature of the adventuring life, however, and would eventually retire into a life of peace. At Sirene's suggestion, the couple built an orphanage together, in which Sirene would care for and raise her wards just as she was raised by the priests of Ilmater. Though Sirene sometime missed the excitement of her previous life, she much preferred the opportunity to live a long life with her beloved <CHARNAME>, as well as the chance to gain the love of her fostered children, who never judged her for her blood as the world did.~

COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/Epilogue/C0Sirzz.2da~ ~override/C0Sir03.2da~
REPLACE ~99999~ ~Though Sirene felt a sense of loss at <CHARNAME>'s ascendency to the Throne of Blood, knowing that it would be unlikely to ever see <PRO_HIMHER> again in her life, she returned to her duty as Ilmater's champion soon afterwards. She never fully recovered from her heartbreak, though she dedicated each life she healed and save to the names of both her deity and her beloved. Those who saw her face under her ever-present white cowl would often tell tales of the sadness in her eyes, until she became known not as a woman cursed with her blood, but a selfless woman with an untold great loss. Sirene continued to help others for her entire life, though she never seemed to form bonds as close as that which she shared with <CHARNAME>. She became weary of battle and bloodshed, putting down her weapon forever. She dedicated her life to building a sanctuary in the underground caverns of Waterdeep, for persecuted outcasts with no home that would accept them. It is assumed that she eventually passed away, though tales still tell of a lady in white wandering the bowels of the City of Splendors, vigilantly guarding her wards for the rest of eternity.~

COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/Epilogue/C0Sirzz.2da~ ~override/C0Sir04.2da~
REPLACE ~99999~ ~Sirene walked away from the events of the Throne of Blood a changed person. Though she knew she would come to miss <CHARNAME> and <PRO_HISHER> companionship, she knew that with the power and confidence she had developed at her beloved friend's side, she would be able to continue her path as Ilmater's loyal knight with her own ability. Sirene learned from <CHARNAME>'s journey that one could become a hero despite the evil in their blood, and discovered in herself a powerful determination to do the same for herself. She returned to her duties as a paladin of the Crying God, bringing peace and healing to many who suffered from pain and persecution. Over time, her deeds became recognized among the people of the Realms, until the Order of the Holy Warrior of Suffering officially welcomed her to Castle Dasaajk as a respected fellow sister-at-arms. Within a few years, her skills at leadership, learned from <CHARNAME>'s example, led to her advancement to Knight-Commander of her order - a role she never wished for, but came to accept nonetheless. She would proceed to live an arduous, yet fulfilling long life, each day of which she would silently thank <CHARNAME> for everything <PRO_HESHE> had done for her.~

COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/Epilogue/C0Sirzz.2da~ ~override/C0Sir05.2da~
REPLACE ~99999~ ~Sirene walked away from the events of the Throne of Blood a changed person. Though she knew she would come to miss <CHARNAME> and <PRO_HISHER> companionship, she knew that with the power and confidence she had developed at her beloved friend's side, she would be able to move on and forge her own destiny with her hands. Sirene learned from <CHARNAME>'s journey that one's heritage did not control them, and discovered in herself the determination to follow her own righteous path - whether the world chose to accept her or not. She knew that despite her forsaking of her duty to Ilmater, her heroic deeds would redeem her to the Holy Warriors of Suffering... but despite that, she decided not to rejoin her order, instead choosing to become a wanderer, seeking and eliminating evil wherever she could. Though few knew of her as the heroine she was, and her name would rarely grace the bardic tales of tavern halls, it mattered not to her - so long as she succeeded in her duty, it mattered not whether she was recognized for it. Sirene eventually became lost to history, and the few who knew her name believed she had fallen in battle - though tales of evil across the Realms falling by a nameless vigilante's hand persisted for many years.~
  
