COPY ~%MOD_FOLDER%/items/c0sbook2.itm~ ~override/c0sbook2.itm~
SAY NAME1 ~Book~
SAY NAME2 ~Ilmatari Tenets of Faith~
SAY DESC ~This book contains several rituals known to high priests of Ilmater. While many are meant for mundane or spiritual purposes and are unsuitable for combat, there are a few which may be useful.

STATISTICS:

Teaches the reader the priest spells 'Favor of Ilmater', 'Endurance of Ilmater' and 'Blast of Pain'
Special: The book is consumed upon use
Usage: Place into quick item slot

-----

Favor of Ilmater
(Necromancy)

Level: 3
Sphere: Necromantic, Protection
Range: 10 ft.
Casting Time: 6
Area of Effect: One creature
Duration: Instant
Saving Throw: None

This spell allows the priest to take on the injuries of another creature, healing 3 hit points per level of the caster and dealing the same amount to <PRO_HIMHER>self as non-lethal damage.

-----

Endurance of Ilmater
(Necromancy)

Level: 4
Sphere: Necromantic, Protection
Range: Touch
Casting Time: 7
Area of Effect: One creature
Duration: 1 round/level
Saving Throw: None

This spell doubles the hit points of the spell recipient for the spell duration. Any damage suffered is taken first from these phantom hit points until they are all exhausted; damage is only then taken from the real hit points of the affected being. The spell also protects the vitality of the spell recipient so that all system shock rolls and checks of any sort against contracting diseases automatically succeed, and all other saving throws receive a +2 bonus. In addition, no being protected by endurance of Ilmater can be knocked over, trampled, ridden down, or overthrown; all protected beings can stand firm against all charges.

-----

Blast of Pain
(Evocation)

Level: 5
Sphere: Combat, Necromantic
Range: 10 ft.
Casting Time: 5
Area of Effect: One creature
Duration: 4 rounds
Saving Throw: Special

This spell creates a beam of smoky gray radiance that streaks unerringly from the priest to a single chosen target who must be within view and range of the caster as casting begins. The target creature must make a saving throw vs. spell at a -5 penalty. If the saving throw is successful, the target is overwhelmed by pain for one round (slowing its movement by half, adding 3 to all casting times, and forcing it to make all attack rolls at a -2 penalty) and suffers 1d4+1 points of non-lethal damage to its nervous system; it is then free of the spell.

If the saving throw is failed, the target creature suffers 4d6 points of non-lethal damage and is stunned and writhing helplessly in pain for the remainder of the current round and the following round. It can make no deliberate attacks, and its awareness of its surroundings is blotted out.

At the beginning of the second round after it was affected, the target being is allowed another saving throw vs. spell, this time at a -4 penalty. If the target succeeds at the saving throw, it suffers 1d4+1 points of non-lethal damage but is then free of the spell. If it fails, 3d6 points of non-lethal damage are inflicted, and the victim continues to be stunned and to writhe helplessly.

At the beginning of the third round after it was affected, the target is allowed a third saving throw vs. spell at a -3 penalty. If the saving throw is successful, the victim suffers 1d4+1 points of non-lethal damage and is then freed from the spell. If the saving throw is failed, 2d6 points of non-lethal damage are inflicted, and the victim continues to be stunned and to writhe helplessly until the end of the round, when the spell ends.

Weight: 2~

